The paper discusses nature-inspired optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the mathematical foundations of these algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the scalability of these algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
